data.chText: （理论、计划等的）解释，说明，阐述
data.enText: a full explanation of a theory, plan, etc.

data.chText: 对他们的法律处境清楚而详尽的说明
data.enText: a clear and detailed exposition of their legal position

data.chText: （产品的）展销；商品交易会；产品博览会
data.enText: an event at which people, businesses, etc. show and sell their goods; a trade fair

simple_means.memory_skill: ex 出 + posit 放，放置 + ion，expose 的名词 → 展览；解释

tr: (music) the section of a movement (especially in sonata form) where the major musical themes first occur
an account that sets forth the meaning or intent of a writing or discourse
example: we would have understood the play better if there had been some initial exposition of the background

tr: a systematic interpretation or explanation (usually written) of a specific topic
a collection of things (goods or works of art etc.) for public display

value.def: An exposition of an idea or theory is a detailed explanation or account of it.

example.ex: The fullest exposition of Coleridge's thought can be found in the States-man's Manual.
example.tran: 柯尔律治的思想可以在《政治家手册》中找到最全面的阐述。

value.def: An exposition is an exhibition in which something such as goods or works of art are shown to the public.
